Next Steps
	Build preprocessing script, save cleaned data on GitHub, begin more exploratory data analysis, and draft first modeling pipeline

Conclusion
	Although I do not have shot by shot data via shotlink/DataGolf exactly like I hoped for, the OpenDataBay dataset provides sufficient round and tournament detail including strokes gained components that will allow meaningful examination of the trade off between aggressiveness and performance in golf. The data is enough to test whether this aggressive play yields higher payoff, and under which conditions.
